Wash and dry all produce. Core, seed, and remove the white ribs from the
@Red Bell Pepper{2%unit}, then thinly slice. Mince or grate the
@Garlic{4%clove}(minced). Finely chop the @Parsley{1/2%ounce}(finely chopped).
Strip the leaves from the @Rosemary{1/4%ounce}(roughly chopped 2 teaspoons)
sprigs. Halve the @Grape Tomatoes{8%ounce}(halved). Dice the
@Dried Chorizo{2%ounce}(diced). Cut the @Chicken Thighs{24%ounce} into
bite-sized pieces and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

In a #medium pot{}, bring 5 cups water and the @Chicken Stock Concentrate{2%unit}
to a simmer. Heat a drizzle of @Olive Oil{2%teaspoon} in a #large pan{}
over medium-high heat. Add the chicken to the pan and cook for
~{1-2%minutes} per side, until browned but not yet cooked through. Remove
from the pan and set aside.

Heat another drizzle of oil in the same #pan{} over medium heat. Add the
chorizo and cook for ~{2-3%minutes}, until slightly crispy. Add the
bell peppers and tomatoes to the pan and cook, tossing for
~{4-5%minutes}, until softened. Add the garlic, chopped rosemary, and half
the parsley to the pan. Cook for another ~{1%minute}, until fragrant.
Season with salt and pepper.

Add the rice: Stir the @Basmati Rice{1.5%cup} into the pan and toss to coat
in the oil. Cook for ~{1-2%minutes}, until the rice is slightly translucent.

Add the chicken and warm chicken stock to the pan and stir to combine.
Season generously with salt and pepper. Bring the mixture to a simmer,
then reduce to a medium-low heat and cook for ~{15-20%minutes}, until the
liquid is absorbed.

> The key to good paella is a browned crust in the bottom of the pan. Don't
> stir the rice!

Finish and serve: Halve the @Lemon{1}, then cut into wedges. Once the liquid
is absorbed, remove the paella from the heat, cover, and set aside for
~{5%minutes}. Serve the chicken and chorizo paella with the remaining parsley
and lemon wedges. Enjoy!